metadata.reasoningText:
Now I understand the structure better. When the welcome view is visible (`.chat-view-welcome-visible`), the interactive session is hidden and the welcome view is shown. 

The issue says "OOTB welcome should show" - so the welcome view is NOT showing when it should be. And there's a "chat input border?" - meaning the chat input border is visible when it shouldn't be.

Let me look at what the `shouldShowWelcome()` logic returns and when the welcome view would be shown:

```typescript
override shouldShowWelcome(): boolean {
    const noPersistedSessions = !this.chatService.hasSessions();
    const hasCoreAgent = this.chatAgentService.getAgents().some(agent => agent.isCore && agent.locations.includes(ChatAgentLocation.Chat));
    const hasDefaultAgent = this.chatAgentService.getDefaultAgent(ChatAgentLocation.Chat) !== undefined;
    const shouldShow = !hasCoreAgent && (!hasDefaultAgent || !this._widget?.viewModel && noPersistedSessions);
    return !!shouldShow;
}
```

So the welcome view displays when there's no core agent and either no default agent exists, or when the widget lacks a viewModel and there are no saved sessions. The logic seems reasonable, but something's preventing the welcome from showing on startup.

