metadata.reasoningText:
Now let me think about the actual fix. The issue says the OOTB welcome should show, and there's a chat input border issue. 

In the OOTB case, the problem is likely in `shouldShowWelcome()` - the `!hasCoreAgent` check prevents the welcome from showing.

But there's another possibility. Looking at the CSS:
```css
.pane-body.chat-view-welcome-visible {
    & > .interactive-session {
        display: none;
    }
    & > .chat-view-welcome {
        display: flex;
    }
}
```

When the welcome IS visible, the interactive session is hidden and the chat-view-welcome is shown. 

I'm realizing ViewPane has its own separate welcome mechanism that might be conflicting with the chat view's welcome logic.

